      "cause": "R3 has no BGP process or neighbor configuration present, so it cannot form any BGP session.",
      "evidence": [
        "R3 running-config excerpt contains an OSPF process (\"\"\"\"\"\"\"\" \"ospf\": { ... \"router-id\": \"3.3.3.3\" } ) and static/default route origination, but there is no BGP/neighbor section in the retrieved configuration for hostname \"R3\".",
        "R3 routing stanza shows only ip-route-interface-forwarding-list (default route via Loopback1) and no BGP-related configuration: '\"routing\": { \"ip-route-interface-forwarding-list\": [ { \"prefix\": \"0.0.0.0\" ... } ] }'."
      ],
      "confidence": 0.95
    },
    {
      "type": "Configuration - missing BGP on peers",
      "cause": "Neighbor routers (R1 and R2) also have no BGP configuration, so even if R3 attempted BGP, peers are not configured to form sessions.",
      "evidence": [
        "R1 running-config shows '\"routing\": null' and an OSPF process (\"ospf\": { ... \"router-id\": \"1.1.1.1\" }), with no BGP section present for hostname \"R1\".",
        "R2 running-config shows '\"routing\": null' and an OSPF process (\"ospf\": { ... \"router-id\": \"2.2.2.2\" }), with no BGP section present for hostname \"R2\"."
      ],
      "confidence": 0.9
    }
  ],
  "missing_info": []
}

